@* Blazor's routing host: a <Router> over this assembly, rendering the matched page.

   Filament has no equivalent of this file, and that difference IS the slice (decision 139). Blazor
   discovers routable components by scanning an ASSEMBLY at run time, so it needs a Router component,
   a RouteView, and reflection over route attributes. Filament knows the whole set of pages at BUILD
   time, so its router is generated from them -- a table and four behaviours, in the app module. *@

<Router AppAssembly="@typeof(Program).Assembly">
    <Found Context="routeData"><RouteView RouteData="@routeData" /></Found>
    <NotFound><p id="missing">not found</p></NotFound>
</Router>
